videos.title: I'm paid to do my job - Wenger
videos.description: Despite yet more calls for him to resign, Arsene Wenger says he will remain fully focused on his job with Arsenal after watching his team beat Stoke 4-1

videos.title: Wenger looking for West Ham favour against Liverpool
videos.description: Now only a point behind Liverpool in the race for UEFA Champions League football, Arsene Wenger is hoping West Ham can beat Jurgen Klopp's men

videos.title: Mahrez penalty a 'freak incident' - Shakespeare
videos.description: Craig Shakespeare has described Riyad Mahrez's penalty miss as a freak incident following Leicester's 2-1 defeat at Manchester City.

videos.title: Shakespeare calls for more video technology after Silva goal
videos.description: Craig Shakespeare believes more video technology should be used in football after David Silva's goal in Manchester City's 2-1 win over Leicester.

videos.title: Gabriel Jesus has 'a lot of things to improve' - Guardiola
videos.description: Pep Guardiola says striker Gabriel Jesus still has a lot of areas to improve on, despite the striker scoring in Manchester City's 2-1 win over Leicester.

videos.title: Guardiola praises 'brave' referee over penalty decision
videos.description: Pep Guardiola says the referee made a brave decision in disallowing Riyad Mahrez's penalty in Manchester City's 2-1 win over Leicester.

videos.title: Allegri congratulates Conte, hails 'king' Ancelotti
videos.description: Massimiliano Allegri hails the achievement of his Italian compatriot, Antonio Conte, at Chelsea, and describes Bayern Munich's Carlo Ancelotti as a 'king'.

videos.title: Chelsea's Premier League title... in numbers
videos.description: A look at some of the key numbers behind Chelsea's Premier League title success.

videos.title: The Amazons preview Reading's play-off clash with Fulham
videos.description: The Amazons preview Reading's play-off clash with Fulham

videos.title: On This Day... Manchester City win the Premier League
videos.description: On this day in 2012 Manchester City clinched the Premier League title with a thrilling last-minute goal from Sergio Aguero.

videos.title: Iheanacho's Man City future to be decided at end of season - Guardiola
videos.description: Pep Guardiola says he'll make a decision on the future of young striker Kelechi Iheanacho at the end of the season.

videos.title: Chelsea deserve title success - Pulis
videos.description: Tony Pulis says Chelsea are worthy Premier League champions after the Blues sealed the title with a 1-0 win at West Brom.

videos.title: Conte targets double after Chelsea clinch title
videos.description: Antonio Conte has already set his sights on the FA Cup after Chelsea clinched their fifth Premier League title.

videos.title: Arsenal defeat the turning point in Chelsea's season - Conte
videos.description: Antonio Conte has described September's defeat at Arsenal as the key moment in Chelsea's title-winning season.

videos.title: Chelsea fans partying a bit hard?
videos.description: Chelsea fans were in party mode in London after the Blues won the title on Friday night at West Brom.

videos.title: Conte living a 'dream' after Chelsea secure title
videos.description: Antonio Conte admits he's living a 'dream' after Chelsea secured a fifth Premier League title on Friday.

videos.title: Chelsea will celebrate after disappointing last season - Conte
videos.description: Chelsea manager Antonio Conte insists the club must celebrate its title success after a disappointing campaign last season.

videos.title: How Chelsea won the title: part 2
videos.description: Chelsea began the year ending a 13 game winning streak, but it wouldn't derail their charge to a fifth Premier League title.

videos.title: Conte 'kidnapped' from his press conference by Luiz and Costa
videos.description: Antonio Conte's Premier League winning press conference was ended abruptly on Friday, after Diego Costa and David Luiz dragged their manager out.

videos.title: Chelsea party starts at final whistle
videos.description: Chelsea fans were in celebratory mode at the final whistle of their match against West Bromwich Albion.

videos.title: How Chelsea won the title: part 1
videos.description: Chelsea are the 2016-17 Premier League champions. It's been quite a journey for Antonio Conte's side, starting from back when Jose Mourinho's second spell at the club ended.

videos.title: Chelsea fans celebrate title-winning goal
videos.description: Chelsea fans erupted in joy after Michy Batshuayi's goal sealed a fifth Premier League title.

videos.title: Conte's work to turn Chelsea into champions
videos.description: The secret to Antonio Conte's impressive debut season as Chelsea manager? Hard work.

videos.title: Everybody loves Antonio Conte
videos.description: Chelsea's Premier League winning manager Antonio Conte has attracted praise from all across Europe after his debut season in English football.

videos.title: Tottenham's new stadium will have the 'soul of White Hart Lane' - Pochettino
videos.description: Mauricio Pochettino says it will be a special day when Tottenham play at White Hart Lane for the final time, but believes the fans are excited by their new stadium.

videos.title: Pochettino plans to watch Chelsea's shot at the title
videos.description: Tottenham manager Mauricio Pochettino says he'll be watching Chelsea's match against West Brom, with the Blues just one match away from the Premier League title.

videos.title: Is FC Metz’s Ismaila Sarr the new Sadio Mané?
videos.description: 19-year-old Ismaila Sarr has drawn comparisons with Liverpool forward Sadio Mané. The two came through the same academy (Generation Foot in Senegal) and started their career at the same Ligue 1 club (Metz). But can Sarr follow the same path as Mané?

videos.title: Man City players' futures already decided - Guardiola
videos.description: Pep Guardiola revealed seven out of contract Man City players, including Yaya Toure, Jesus Navas and Willy Caballero, have already had their futures decided.

videos.title: Guardiola will get Yaya Toure 'the biggest' birthday cake
videos.description: Pep Guardiola will get Yaya Toure 'the biggest cake ever' when the midfielder turns 34 on Saturday.

videos.title: Top four finish will dictate Liverpool transfers - Klopp
videos.description: Jurgen Klopp admits whether Liverpool finish in the top four or not will have a big effect on the club's transfer policy.

videos.title: Klopp relaxed over top four pressure
videos.description: Liverpool manager Jurgen Klopp insists the pressure is a good thing ahead of the crucial Premier League clash with West Ham.

videos.title: Man United's season a success without Europa League - Mourinho
videos.description: Jose Mourinho believes it will be a successful season for Manchester United, even if they don't win the UEFA Europa League.
